    "abstract": "<jats:p>We estimate the sensitivity of Internet retail purchasing to sales taxes using eBay data. Our first approach exploits the fact that a seller's location\u2014and therefore the applicable tax rate\u2014is revealed only after a buyer has expressed interest in an item. We document how adverse tax \u201csurprises\u201d reduce the likelihood of purchase and shift subsequent purchases toward out-of-state sellers. We then use more aggregated data to estimate that every one percentage point increase in a state's sales tax increases online purchases by state residents by almost 2 percent, while decreasing their online purchases from state retailers by 3\u20134 percent. (JEL H71, L81, L86)</jats:p>",
